# {{ site.businessName }} — Sub-Metering for Landlords

> {{ site.businessName }} installs clip-on electricity sub-meters in multi-unit rental properties across {{ site.serviceArea }}. Landlords with shared meters lose $300+ per month subsidizing tenants' hydro. We fix that.

## What We Do

{{ site.businessName }} installs clip-on sub-meters (current transformers) that give each unit in a multi-unit property its own electricity measurement. The meters clamp around existing wiring without touching it — no rewiring, no cutting, no damage, no permits required. Installation takes under 1 hour. Tenants pay for what they use. Landlords stop subsidizing hydro.

## What This Is NOT

This is not electrical work. We do not cut wires, modify panels, or rewire anything. The device is a clip-on current transformer — it clamps around the cable like a clamp. No ESA certification required. No permits needed. No power shutoff during installation. 100% reversible — remove the clip and the panel goes back to exactly how it was.

